# Overview

Ten Lives positions itself as:
- a **movement of festivals** that regenerates land :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}
- a “grass-root movement” building a “great blue wall of hydrated landscapes against desertification” :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}

## What Ten Lives does (public description)
A Ten Lives event is described as a **7-day** experience built around:
- **guided regeneration work** in the mornings
- **workshops & talks** in the afternoons
- **music & shows** and immersive experiences :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}
